1
00:00:06,101 --> 00:00:10,272
Look at this. These amazing figures.

2
00:00:10,355 --> 00:00:13,400
And these beautiful dioramas.

3
00:00:14,359 --> 00:00:16,320
This is amazing!

4
00:00:16,403 --> 00:00:19,781
Right? Right? The creator is Masahiro Kitajima.

5
00:00:20,282 --> 00:00:23,327
He's the modeler who's getting the most attention right now.

6
00:00:23,410 --> 00:00:27,414
Hmm... It's all so tiny, I don't really get it.

7
00:00:27,497 --> 00:00:31,793
Ah, how unfortunate. Not understanding this technique...

8
00:00:31,877 --> 00:00:33,295
What do you think, Conan-kun?

9
00:00:33,670 --> 00:00:36,256
I don't know much about the trains,

10
00:00:36,340 --> 00:00:39,301
but the dioramas are definitely amazing.

11
00:00:39,384 --> 00:00:42,512
Every single branch is reproduced perfectly.

12
00:00:42,596 --> 00:00:44,431
As expected of Conan-kun.

13
00:00:44,514 --> 00:00:48,560
Kitajima-san is called a genius when it comes to natural forms.

14
00:00:48,977 --> 00:00:53,190
On top of that, he's been selected to exhibit at this year's world championship...

15
00:00:53,273 --> 00:00:55,525
Ah, Kitajima-san!

16
00:00:55,943 --> 00:00:58,445
You're Masahiro Kitajima-san, right?

17
00:00:58,528 --> 00:01:01,490
How do you make such amazing figures?

18
00:01:01,823 --> 00:01:05,160
Well... I guess it's imagination.

19
00:01:05,243 --> 00:01:07,704
The richer your imagination,

20
00:01:07,788 --> 00:01:09,498
the better figures you can make.

21
00:01:09,831 --> 00:01:12,542
I see. Imagination...

22
00:01:12,626 --> 00:01:14,169
Masahiro-san.

23
00:01:14,461 --> 00:01:17,547
Ah, Reika, you came.

24
00:01:17,631 --> 00:01:19,925
Of course. This is your big day.

25
00:01:20,175 --> 00:01:23,178
Cut it out. People are watching.

26
00:01:23,470 --> 00:01:25,639
Hey, hey, you kids. Ah...

27
00:01:26,098 --> 00:01:27,933
Come take a look at my figure too.

28
00:01:29,685 --> 00:01:31,895
Wow, it's beautiful!

29
00:01:32,479 --> 00:01:34,648
The colors are so pretty.

30
00:01:34,731 --> 00:01:36,775
Haha... yeah, I guess.

31
00:01:37,401 --> 00:01:39,319
I'm sure you all know this too,

32
00:01:39,403 --> 00:01:42,280
but this is from the most popular robot anime right now.

33
00:01:42,656 --> 00:01:43,657
Huh?

34
00:01:44,157 --> 00:01:47,369
I made it working all night. Pretty amazing, right?

35
00:01:47,452 --> 00:01:50,038
A grown adult doing this... Huh?

36
00:01:50,580 --> 00:01:54,126
Yes. On this day, at this convention hall,

37
00:01:54,209 --> 00:01:57,045
the Figure Model Festival was being held,

38
00:01:57,129 --> 00:02:00,674
and we had come to see it.

39
00:02:01,466 --> 00:02:07,472
♪~♪

40
00:02:14,438 --> 00:02:18,066
The blackness of shadows, the density of darkness—
the light of reasoning cuts right through them.

41
00:02:18,150 --> 00:02:21,903
An incident occurs at the event hall.
The secret hidden in the figures.

42
00:02:21,987 --> 00:02:23,488
See through the one and only truth.

43
00:02:23,572 --> 00:02:25,365
Looks like a kid, but has the mind of an adult.

44
00:02:25,449 --> 00:02:28,201
His name is Detective Conan!

45
00:03:52,825 --> 00:03:58,831
♪~♪

46
00:04:00,612 --> 00:04:05,712
"A Much Too Perfect Figurine"

47
00:04:08,257 --> 00:04:11,552
Hey, Mitsuhiko, let's go home already.

48
00:04:11,635 --> 00:04:12,928
I'm hungry.

49
00:04:13,011 --> 00:04:14,513
Wait a minute.

50
00:04:14,596 --> 00:04:18,141
What color would match the Kamen Yaiba I'm making now...

51
00:04:18,225 --> 00:04:19,768
(Female staff screams) Whoa...

52
00:04:19,852 --> 00:04:21,770
Someone!

53
00:04:22,980 --> 00:04:24,189
Conan-kun?

54
00:04:27,818 --> 00:04:28,986
Ah...

55
00:04:32,406 --> 00:04:33,448
Whoa!

56
00:04:35,117 --> 00:04:36,785
H-hey, Conan.

57
00:04:37,953 --> 00:04:40,205
One stab in the chest with a blade, huh?

58
00:04:40,455 --> 00:04:42,416
Hmm? This person...

59
00:04:44,376 --> 00:04:46,420
Kitajima-san? Ah.

60
00:04:46,503 --> 00:04:48,088
(Hiroto Kenji panting) (Female staff screams)

61
00:04:48,171 --> 00:04:49,923
Stop! Move!

62
00:04:50,674 --> 00:04:51,758
Ah!

63
00:04:52,134 --> 00:04:53,468
Ugh... ah...

64
00:04:55,178 --> 00:04:57,347
Ah, ah, ahhh...

65
00:04:57,764 --> 00:04:59,766
Are you okay, Haibara? Ayumi?

66
00:05:00,017 --> 00:05:03,979
Yeah, I'm okay. Ai-chan saved me.

67
00:05:04,062 --> 00:05:06,106
...Geez, get it together.

68
00:05:06,648 --> 00:05:07,983
Sorry, sorry.

69
00:05:09,693 --> 00:05:12,154
We heard the staff member's scream,

70
00:05:12,696 --> 00:05:16,825
and when we rushed over, this Kitajima-san was collapsed on the ground.

71
00:05:16,909 --> 00:05:18,452
...is that right?

72
00:05:18,785 --> 00:05:21,455
Yeah, we found him.

73
00:05:21,538 --> 00:05:24,458
The victim is Masahiro Kitajima-san.

74
00:05:24,541 --> 00:05:25,542
That's right.

75
00:05:25,626 --> 00:05:28,462
He's one of Japan's top modelers.

76
00:05:28,962 --> 00:05:31,924
Hmm... Top modeler?

77
00:05:32,215 --> 00:05:34,509
A professional who makes plastic models.

78
00:05:35,052 --> 00:05:36,428
Hmm... Ahahaha...

79
00:05:36,511 --> 00:05:38,430
Ah, okay, okay.

80
00:05:38,722 --> 00:05:40,891
You kids should go home now.

81
00:05:40,974 --> 00:05:44,895
That's not fair. We even caught the culprit, you know?

82
00:05:44,978 --> 00:05:46,855
Ai-chan did, right?

83
00:05:46,939 --> 00:05:48,523
Chief Megure. Hmm?

84
00:05:48,607 --> 00:05:50,442
We've brought Hiroto-san.

85
00:05:50,525 --> 00:05:51,526
Yes.

86
00:05:51,610 --> 00:05:53,904
Ah! It's this man.

87
00:05:53,987 --> 00:05:56,239
There's no doubt he's the culprit.

88
00:05:56,323 --> 00:05:58,492
Hmm... Ah, whoa!

89
00:05:59,159 --> 00:06:01,620
His name is Kenji Hiroto.

90
00:06:01,703 --> 00:06:04,289
He's apparently an editor for a plastic model magazine.

91
00:06:04,748 --> 00:06:06,541
There's no mistake about it.

92
00:06:06,625 --> 00:06:09,628
That's right. I've been saying it from the start.

93
00:06:09,711 --> 00:06:13,173
I just came to interview Kitajima.

94
00:06:13,256 --> 00:06:15,968
Then why did you run away?

95
00:06:16,051 --> 00:06:19,638
Ah, I... was just surprised.

96
00:06:19,721 --> 00:06:22,891
I mean, Kitajima was in that state...

97
00:06:23,517 --> 00:06:26,561
Um... is this man not the culprit?

98
00:06:26,645 --> 00:06:29,690
No, he wasn't carrying any weapon.

99
00:06:29,773 --> 00:06:32,734
Huh? More importantly, Agasa-hakase,

100
00:06:33,151 --> 00:06:36,989
it's probably best not to bring the children to places like this...

101
00:06:37,072 --> 00:06:40,117
Ah, I understand. Come on, everyone, let's go home.

102
00:06:40,200 --> 00:06:42,327
Huh? Come on, let's go.

103
00:06:42,411 --> 00:06:44,246
But it's just getting started! What a bummer.

104
00:06:44,329 --> 00:06:45,998
Sorry about this, everyone.

105
00:06:46,081 --> 00:06:47,708
Hey, Takagi-keiji.

106
00:06:47,791 --> 00:06:51,545
From when Kitajima-san died until we found him,

107
00:06:51,628 --> 00:06:53,714
how much time had passed?

108
00:06:53,797 --> 00:06:56,425
Ah... a few minutes.

109
00:06:56,800 --> 00:06:59,177
The weapon was definitely a sharp blade?

110
00:06:59,261 --> 00:07:02,222
Yeah, some kind of knife.

111
00:07:02,556 --> 00:07:04,141
But you still haven't found it?

112
00:07:04,224 --> 00:07:07,394
Yeah, we've been searching.

113
00:07:07,686 --> 00:07:10,272
What about the staff member who came to bring tea?

114
00:07:10,355 --> 00:07:13,233
She didn't have anything like that.

115
00:07:14,276 --> 00:07:16,903
The weapon hasn't been found...

116
00:07:17,154 --> 00:07:19,781
He's definitely the culprit. No question about it.

117
00:07:19,865 --> 00:07:22,200
I wonder. Huh?

118
00:07:22,284 --> 00:07:25,871
From when Kitajima-san was killed until he was found,

119
00:07:25,954 --> 00:07:27,706
only a few minutes passed.

120
00:07:28,040 --> 00:07:31,960
If that man is the culprit, there's a high chance he still has the weapon.

121
00:07:32,294 --> 00:07:35,464
Or he hid it somewhere nearby.

122
00:07:35,547 --> 00:07:37,049
But there's no sign of it anywhere...

123
00:07:37,132 --> 00:07:38,633
I see.

124
00:07:38,717 --> 00:07:41,470
Where did the weapon go?

125
00:07:41,553 --> 00:07:45,766
Um, detective... what should I do?

126
00:07:46,058 --> 00:07:47,768
Ah, sorry.

127
00:07:47,851 --> 00:07:50,353
The inspector wants to speak with you,

128
00:07:50,437 --> 00:07:51,772
so please wait a little longer.

129
00:07:52,230 --> 00:07:54,274
Huh? It's the robot guy.

130
00:07:54,357 --> 00:07:56,985
Ah, you kids were here too.

131
00:07:57,069 --> 00:07:58,779
What's wrong, mister?

132
00:07:58,862 --> 00:08:03,325
Well, I was in the waiting room over there the whole time.

133
00:08:03,408 --> 00:08:05,660
Then I heard a commotion,

134
00:08:05,744 --> 00:08:08,246
and when I went outside, there was a staff member,

135
00:08:08,330 --> 00:08:11,333
and they told me something terrible had happened to Kitajima-san...

136
00:08:11,666 --> 00:08:14,419
And you've been with that staff member ever since?

137
00:08:14,503 --> 00:08:16,338
Huh? Uh...

138
00:08:16,421 --> 00:08:20,133
Ah, yes. This man was with that staff member the whole time.

139
00:08:20,634 --> 00:08:23,261
Was there a knife near Morishita-san?

140
00:08:23,345 --> 00:08:26,431
No, neither he nor the waiting room had one.

141
00:08:27,182 --> 00:08:29,434
So this man isn't the culprit either.

142
00:08:29,768 --> 00:08:32,896
Ah, if it isn't Morishita.

143
00:08:32,979 --> 00:08:34,147
Hiroto-san.

144
00:08:34,981 --> 00:08:38,610
Did you kill Kitajima-san? Wasn't it Hiroto-san?

145
00:08:38,693 --> 00:08:40,320
Huh? Huh?

146
00:08:40,403 --> 00:08:41,863
Wha... what?

147
00:08:42,155 --> 00:08:44,616
You do some harsh interviews, you know.

148
00:08:44,699 --> 00:08:48,203
Taking figures without permission, touching them even when told not to.

149
00:08:48,620 --> 00:08:50,914
Kitajima-san told all the other modelers

150
00:08:50,997 --> 00:08:54,334
to never agree to be interviewed by you.

151
00:08:54,417 --> 00:08:57,212
Hmph. Look who's talking, Morishita.

152
00:08:57,295 --> 00:08:59,297
You're suspicious too.

153
00:08:59,381 --> 00:09:03,009
I heard you borrowed quite a bit of money from Kitajima.

154
00:09:03,426 --> 00:09:08,014
And you couldn't pay it back for years, so he was putting pressure on you.

155
00:09:08,431 --> 00:09:09,850
Shut up! Be quiet!

156
00:09:09,933 --> 00:09:11,143
(Footsteps) Hmm?

157
00:09:11,226 --> 00:09:15,105
Masahiro-san, is it true? Was Masahiro-san killed?

158
00:09:15,188 --> 00:09:16,439
Ah, hey, you...

159
00:09:16,523 --> 00:09:18,525
Masahiro-san, Masahiro-san!

160
00:09:18,608 --> 00:09:22,529
Masahiro-san... ugh, why...?

161
00:09:22,612 --> 00:09:24,698
Here comes the main suspect. Hmm?

162
00:09:26,491 --> 00:09:30,327
I wondered who it was, but it's Hiroto-san. And Morishita-san too.

163
00:09:30,620 --> 00:09:33,039
You two are the culprits, aren't you? Huh?

164
00:09:33,415 --> 00:09:35,333
Give me a break.

165
00:09:35,417 --> 00:09:39,421
I heard you were having a rough time with a breakup recently too.

166
00:09:40,046 --> 00:09:43,258
A breakup? That's...

167
00:09:43,341 --> 00:09:47,053
Masahiro-san and I even promised to get married.

168
00:09:47,137 --> 00:09:48,763
I doubt it.

169
00:09:48,847 --> 00:09:51,725
Morishita, you've heard about it too, right?

170
00:09:51,808 --> 00:09:53,935
Huh? Ah... well...

171
00:09:54,227 --> 00:09:55,437
You kids.

172
00:09:56,021 --> 00:09:58,106
Hakase, please take the children...

173
00:09:58,190 --> 00:09:59,858
Ah, sorry.

174
00:09:59,941 --> 00:10:01,568
Come on, let's go. (Detective Boys chatter)

175
00:10:01,860 --> 00:10:04,738
Come on, hurry up. We're going home.

176
00:10:04,821 --> 00:10:07,449
Ah... and we were just getting started.

177
00:10:07,866 --> 00:10:11,578
I thought we were finally about to corner the culprit.

178
00:10:11,661 --> 00:10:13,663
Huh? Where's Conan-kun?

179
00:10:14,039 --> 00:10:15,916
Huh? ...What?

180
00:10:17,918 --> 00:10:19,794
Reika Kameyama-san.

181
00:10:20,170 --> 00:10:23,715
Where were you when the incident occurred?

182
00:10:23,798 --> 00:10:25,300
I was outside.

183
00:10:25,759 --> 00:10:30,305
After we met at the venue, Masahiro-san contacted me by email.

184
00:10:30,722 --> 00:10:34,392
He said, "Wait for me at the river plaza next to the hall."

185
00:10:34,684 --> 00:10:37,854
But Masahiro-san never came, no matter how long I waited,

186
00:10:37,938 --> 00:10:39,814
so I came to the waiting room, and...

187
00:10:40,315 --> 00:10:41,858
this...

188
00:10:41,942 --> 00:10:44,694
Indeed, an email was sent from Kitajima-san's phone

189
00:10:44,778 --> 00:10:47,781
addressed to Reika-san.

190
00:10:48,073 --> 00:10:52,410
11:25 AM. Ten minutes before the incident occurred.

191
00:10:52,911 --> 00:10:54,454
That means...

192
00:10:54,537 --> 00:10:57,207
after sending this email,

193
00:10:57,290 --> 00:10:58,792
Kitajima-san was killed.

194
00:11:00,585 --> 00:11:02,796
Hmm? Hey, Conan.

195
00:11:03,630 --> 00:11:04,965
The police officers?

196
00:11:05,048 --> 00:11:07,592
Yeah, they're making a fuss over there.

197
00:11:07,676 --> 00:11:10,679
Can you reach it? No.

198
00:11:10,929 --> 00:11:13,932
Officer, what's wrong? Huh?

199
00:11:14,391 --> 00:11:18,687
Ah, something fell between the vending machine and the wall,

200
00:11:18,770 --> 00:11:20,063
and we can't reach it.

201
00:11:20,146 --> 00:11:23,817
I'm small, so I think I can reach it. Leave it to me.

202
00:11:26,069 --> 00:11:29,364
Ugh... grr...

203
00:11:31,658 --> 00:11:32,784
That's it, right?

204
00:11:33,285 --> 00:11:34,452
Genta, a handkerchief.

205
00:11:34,536 --> 00:11:36,663
Oh? Oh... yeah.

206
00:11:38,873 --> 00:11:41,543
Okay, here we go... ugh...

207
00:11:44,838 --> 00:11:46,381
Okay, nice, Genta.

208
00:11:46,589 --> 00:11:48,383
Okay, got it.

209
00:11:50,176 --> 00:11:51,553
Oh!

210
00:11:54,097 --> 00:11:55,348
This is...

211
00:11:56,891 --> 00:11:58,226
Bloodstains?

212
00:12:09,361 --> 00:12:10,529
Kameyama-san.

213
00:12:11,030 --> 00:12:14,408
Do you recognize this brooch?

214
00:12:14,658 --> 00:12:17,912
Huh? Ah... yes, it's mine.

215
00:12:18,162 --> 00:12:20,331
There were faint bloodstains on it.

216
00:12:20,414 --> 00:12:24,668
According to forensics, it's definitely Kitajima-san's blood.

217
00:12:24,752 --> 00:12:28,756
Ah, no way. That brooch, since yesterday...

218
00:12:28,964 --> 00:12:31,634
Yes, I couldn't find it since yesterday...

219
00:12:31,717 --> 00:12:33,427
When yesterday?

220
00:12:33,761 --> 00:12:37,515
At night. I brought a celebration bouquet.

221
00:12:37,598 --> 00:12:39,266
From that time on...

222
00:12:39,558 --> 00:12:43,479
Um... I just remembered something.

223
00:12:43,854 --> 00:12:47,316
Actually... I saw it.

224
00:12:47,858 --> 00:12:50,861
No! I'm never breaking up with you!

225
00:12:51,362 --> 00:12:52,446
I'm going to...

226
00:12:52,530 --> 00:12:55,825
go out into the world as a modeler from now on.

227
00:12:56,116 --> 00:12:58,160
You're in the way.

228
00:12:58,244 --> 00:12:59,662
That's...

229
00:13:00,246 --> 00:13:02,456
Was that your plan from the beginning?

230
00:13:03,499 --> 00:13:04,542
Hmph.

231
00:13:05,417 --> 00:13:06,460
How cruel.

232
00:13:08,170 --> 00:13:11,507
I'll never forgive you. I'll kill you.

233
00:13:12,466 --> 00:13:15,261
Is that true, Kameyama-san?

234
00:13:15,469 --> 00:13:18,013
Ah... y-yes, I said that.

235
00:13:18,430 --> 00:13:20,224
But I didn't do it.

236
00:13:20,307 --> 00:13:22,685
Hahaha... Ah.

237
00:13:22,768 --> 00:13:26,480
So you're the culprit after all. Is that how it went?

238
00:13:27,106 --> 00:13:30,734
You received the email. You were afraid of being broken up with,

239
00:13:30,818 --> 00:13:32,570
so you went to the waiting room.

240
00:13:32,653 --> 00:13:34,989
But in the end, you got into an argument...

241
00:13:45,165 --> 00:13:46,417
After that, you

242
00:13:46,500 --> 00:13:50,296
immediately went outside and pretended to be waiting for Kitajima,

243
00:13:50,379 --> 00:13:53,340
and threw the weapon into the river. I see.

244
00:13:53,841 --> 00:13:57,511
Kameyama-san, we'll need to hear more details from you.

245
00:13:57,595 --> 00:13:59,930
It seems necessary.

246
00:14:00,014 --> 00:14:02,224
But... I didn't do it.

247
00:14:03,309 --> 00:14:04,476
Ah.

248
00:14:07,563 --> 00:14:11,650
Ah... so that woman is the culprit.

249
00:14:11,734 --> 00:14:13,485
But it's a little frustrating.

250
00:14:13,569 --> 00:14:17,781
Yeah. They treated us like children until the very end.

251
00:14:17,865 --> 00:14:21,285
Damn it. I'll take out this anger on dinner.

252
00:14:21,827 --> 00:14:25,039
A brooch... blood spatter...

253
00:14:36,592 --> 00:14:38,510
It's still strange.

254
00:14:38,761 --> 00:14:40,930
Hey, kids. Ah.

255
00:14:41,263 --> 00:14:44,058
Nice footwork, little lady.

256
00:14:44,141 --> 00:14:45,684
Oh, thank you.

257
00:14:45,768 --> 00:14:48,646
What, did you come to get revenge?

258
00:14:48,729 --> 00:14:49,939
Stop it.

259
00:14:50,022 --> 00:14:51,941
I don't feel like fighting.

260
00:14:52,691 --> 00:14:55,069
Believe it or not, I'm actually feeling down.

261
00:14:55,152 --> 00:14:57,571
I missed out on a scandal.

262
00:14:57,905 --> 00:15:01,867
Scandal? Do you mean about Kitajima-san?

263
00:15:01,951 --> 00:15:04,078
Mister, what is this scandal?

264
00:15:04,370 --> 00:15:08,582
Whoa, that's none of you kids' business. See ya.

265
00:15:08,832 --> 00:15:10,250
Ah...

266
00:15:10,334 --> 00:15:12,252
Ah... I see, I see.

267
00:15:12,670 --> 00:15:13,921
Wait a minute, please.

268
00:15:14,672 --> 00:15:15,756
What?

269
00:15:16,090 --> 00:15:20,052
To these kids, Kitajima-san was a hero.

270
00:15:20,135 --> 00:15:23,097
If that man had any hidden secrets,

271
00:15:23,180 --> 00:15:25,265
won't you tell us?

272
00:15:25,599 --> 00:15:29,019
Hmph. Dreams are best kept as dreams, you know?

273
00:15:29,103 --> 00:15:31,355
No, I think knowing the truth

274
00:15:31,438 --> 00:15:34,942
would be much better for these kids.

275
00:15:35,025 --> 00:15:39,279
Well, I guess it's fine. The guy's dead anyway.

276
00:15:39,363 --> 00:15:41,281
The truth is, there were rumors

277
00:15:41,365 --> 00:15:45,244
that Kitajima had someone making figures for him.

278
00:15:45,327 --> 00:15:47,413
Huh? Making figures for him?

279
00:15:47,705 --> 00:15:50,874
Yeah. His natural forms

280
00:15:50,958 --> 00:15:53,961
were outstanding, even among modelers.

281
00:15:54,044 --> 00:15:56,588
But originally, he wasn't that skilled

282
00:15:56,672 --> 00:15:59,216
of a modeler.

283
00:15:59,299 --> 00:16:02,052
But then, in the past few years, suddenly...

284
00:16:02,720 --> 00:16:04,013
On top of that,

285
00:16:04,096 --> 00:16:07,558
he's never let anyone watch him make a figure.

286
00:16:07,641 --> 00:16:11,270
I see. So that's why you snuck into the waiting room

287
00:16:11,353 --> 00:16:13,230
to confirm it?

288
00:16:13,313 --> 00:16:14,314
Yeah.

289
00:16:17,526 --> 00:16:21,447
That's right. I've been bothered by something

290
00:16:21,530 --> 00:16:23,699
from the moment we arrived at this venue.

291
00:16:23,991 --> 00:16:25,409
Hmm?

292
00:16:26,618 --> 00:16:28,954
Conan-kun, what's wrong?

293
00:16:29,246 --> 00:16:30,748
Is it this?

294
00:16:31,290 --> 00:16:32,583
Hey, Mitsuhiko.

295
00:16:32,666 --> 00:16:36,170
Doesn't this color look like the one in Kitajima-san's diorama?

296
00:16:36,253 --> 00:16:39,465
Huh? Ah, it's Kamen Yaiba.

297
00:16:39,548 --> 00:16:43,148
I'm using the same color for the Yaiba I'm making now.

298
00:16:43,886 --> 00:16:45,929
So the finish is also...

299
00:16:46,180 --> 00:16:49,016
Yes, no doubt about it. It's the same color.

300
00:16:49,308 --> 00:16:52,144
I see. So that's how it is.

301
00:16:52,227 --> 00:16:55,189
Hmm? Ah... huh? You kids are still here?

302
00:16:55,272 --> 00:16:58,025
Go home already... wait?

303
00:16:58,609 --> 00:17:01,278
No, I mean, Agasa-hakase.

304
00:17:01,361 --> 00:17:04,531
What is this? Why did you suddenly gather everyone?

305
00:17:05,199 --> 00:17:07,951
Sorry to suddenly call you all together.

306
00:17:08,410 --> 00:17:09,995
Regarding this case,

307
00:17:10,079 --> 00:17:13,624
there are several things that bother me.

308
00:17:13,707 --> 00:17:18,128
First, Reika-san's brooch that was found in the hallway.

309
00:17:19,129 --> 00:17:22,132
The brooch had Kitajima-san's blood on it.

310
00:17:22,466 --> 00:17:25,427
But take a close look at her clothes.

311
00:17:25,511 --> 00:17:27,638
There's no blood anywhere on them.

312
00:17:28,013 --> 00:17:30,099
Would blood spatter from stabbing someone

313
00:17:30,182 --> 00:17:34,144
only get on the brooch and nowhere else?

314
00:17:34,561 --> 00:17:38,524
Then someone put blood on the brooch

315
00:17:38,607 --> 00:17:41,443
to frame her?

316
00:17:41,527 --> 00:17:43,237
But that's...

317
00:17:43,320 --> 00:17:46,156
And there's another strange thing.

318
00:17:46,240 --> 00:17:47,241
Huh?

319
00:17:47,324 --> 00:17:50,119
Regarding you, Morishita-san.

320
00:17:50,202 --> 00:17:51,495
Huh? Me?

321
00:17:51,829 --> 00:17:55,290
Yes. When I first met you,

322
00:17:55,541 --> 00:17:57,584
you said it was from a popular robot anime,

323
00:17:57,668 --> 00:18:01,338
and that you made it working all night. Your clothes were

324
00:18:01,421 --> 00:18:03,006
stained with paint.

325
00:18:03,465 --> 00:18:06,301
Yes, that outfit. However...

326
00:18:06,385 --> 00:18:08,303
(Footsteps) Hmm?

327
00:18:11,640 --> 00:18:14,309
Take a look at that robot.

328
00:18:14,810 --> 00:18:18,730
It was made by Morishita-san. The colors are vivid.

329
00:18:18,814 --> 00:18:21,692
They're completely different from the colors on his clothes.

330
00:18:21,775 --> 00:18:23,318
Why is that?

331
00:18:23,694 --> 00:18:26,572
Inside Morishita-san's paint case,

332
00:18:26,655 --> 00:18:29,825
there was paint the same color as the stains on his clothes.

333
00:18:30,075 --> 00:18:31,410
This is it.

334
00:18:31,994 --> 00:18:35,247
And for some reason, this color is the same

335
00:18:35,330 --> 00:18:38,834
as the color used in Kitajima-san's dioramas.

336
00:18:39,293 --> 00:18:42,212
There were rumors that Kitajima-san

337
00:18:42,296 --> 00:18:44,214
had someone making figures for him.

338
00:18:44,882 --> 00:18:47,301
Morishita-san, wasn't it you?

339
00:18:47,384 --> 00:18:49,344
The one making them for him.

340
00:18:49,428 --> 00:18:53,015
Y-yes, that's right. I was forced to make them.

341
00:18:53,515 --> 00:18:57,644
My mother was sick, so I borrowed money from Kitajima.

342
00:18:57,728 --> 00:19:01,732
But the interest was outrageous, and the debt grew until I couldn't pay it back.

343
00:19:02,274 --> 00:19:04,026
Then that guy...

344
00:19:04,568 --> 00:19:06,528
In that case, Morishita,

345
00:19:06,612 --> 00:19:10,407
make my share too, okay?

346
00:19:10,991 --> 00:19:13,493
And on top of that, Kitajima-san was planning

347
00:19:13,577 --> 00:19:16,330
to enter the world championship with your figures.

348
00:19:16,413 --> 00:19:19,499
That must have made you hate him.

349
00:19:19,583 --> 00:19:22,211
So you killed Kitajima-san.

350
00:19:22,294 --> 00:19:25,714
No! That has nothing to do with this incident.

351
00:19:25,964 --> 00:19:28,383
But if that's the case,

352
00:19:28,467 --> 00:19:30,928
everything fits together perfectly.

353
00:19:31,720 --> 00:19:33,513
Last night,

354
00:19:33,597 --> 00:19:37,434
you happened to see Kitajima-san and Reika-san arguing.

355
00:19:37,893 --> 00:19:40,604
At that time, you picked up the brooch

356
00:19:40,687 --> 00:19:42,731
that Reika-san dropped as she left.

357
00:19:45,484 --> 00:19:48,737
Then today, you killed Kitajima-san,

358
00:19:48,987 --> 00:19:51,156
got his blood on the brooch,

359
00:19:51,240 --> 00:19:54,743
and threw it behind the vending machine in the hallway

360
00:19:54,952 --> 00:19:58,163
to frame Reika-san.

361
00:19:58,830 --> 00:20:02,209
Of course, you didn't forget to call Reika-san by email

362
00:20:02,292 --> 00:20:05,587
to eliminate her alibi.

363
00:20:06,171 --> 00:20:10,092
Ha, hahaha...

364
00:20:10,175 --> 00:20:11,802
Haha, hahaha... Huh?

365
00:20:11,885 --> 00:20:13,804
Give me a break.

366
00:20:14,304 --> 00:20:17,766
You're not seriously buying this nonsense, are you?

367
00:20:17,849 --> 00:20:19,309
I didn't do it.

368
00:20:19,685 --> 00:20:23,522
That's right. The weapon. Where is the weapon?

369
00:20:23,605 --> 00:20:26,316
I didn't have anything like that on me.

370
00:20:26,566 --> 00:20:28,902
When it comes to natural forms,

371
00:20:28,986 --> 00:20:32,239
Kitajima-san was said to be a genius.

372
00:20:32,656 --> 00:20:34,116
But the truth is, that was you,

373
00:20:34,199 --> 00:20:37,995
the one making them for him.

374
00:20:38,245 --> 00:20:43,000
Inside your paint case, there was a color like this.

375
00:20:43,333 --> 00:20:45,252
Natural Light Green.

376
00:20:45,335 --> 00:20:48,005
I know it because it's used on Kamen Yaiba too.

377
00:20:48,088 --> 00:20:52,467
There's one natural thing of the same color in this room.

378
00:20:52,551 --> 00:20:54,261
Everyone, which one is it?

379
00:20:54,761 --> 00:20:55,929
That one! That one!

380
00:21:01,810 --> 00:21:03,687
Ah, ah...

381
00:21:05,355 --> 00:21:08,692
I'll never forgive you. I'll kill you.

382
00:21:09,151 --> 00:21:11,153
Kitajima-san said

383
00:21:11,236 --> 00:21:13,655
that the important thing for making figures

384
00:21:13,739 --> 00:21:16,533
is to have a rich imagination.

385
00:21:17,284 --> 00:21:20,120
So you imagined it too, didn't you, Morishita-san?

386
00:21:20,495 --> 00:21:24,624
Seeing these flowers that Reika-san brought.

387
00:21:24,708 --> 00:21:26,376
(Metal sound) Ah.

388
00:21:30,130 --> 00:21:31,631
Ah.

389
00:21:34,092 --> 00:21:35,510
I see.

390
00:21:35,594 --> 00:21:38,889
You painted the blade in advance and then committed the crime...

391
00:21:39,222 --> 00:21:41,725
It's all Kitajima's fault.

392
00:21:41,808 --> 00:21:44,895
He told me to make them for him, so I...

393
00:21:45,937 --> 00:21:49,274
I'm not the bad one!

394
00:21:49,358 --> 00:21:51,860
(Crying)

395
00:21:52,277 --> 00:21:58,283
♪~♪

396
00:23:06,059 --> 00:23:11,815
♪~♪

397
00:23:12,732 --> 00:23:15,068
Everyone praised us like crazy.

398
00:23:15,152 --> 00:23:17,654
And they even gave us these plastic models.

399
00:23:17,737 --> 00:23:19,656
That's great.

400
00:23:19,739 --> 00:23:21,283
But still...

401
00:23:21,533 --> 00:23:22,659
Okay.

402
00:23:23,160 --> 00:23:24,786
Conan-kun, please.

403
00:23:24,870 --> 00:23:26,079
Huh? Me too.

404
00:23:26,163 --> 00:23:28,081
I'm making Yaiba right now.

405
00:23:28,165 --> 00:23:30,167
Once I make it, I'll get hungry.

406
00:23:30,250 --> 00:23:32,169
Haha. Food, food!

407
00:23:32,252 --> 00:23:35,464
H-hey, wait a minute. Make them yourselves.

408
00:23:35,839 --> 00:23:37,841
Whether it's four or five,

409
00:23:37,924 --> 00:23:39,551
it's the same, right? Huh?

410
00:23:39,634 --> 00:23:42,762
Ah, ah, ah... Haah... Food, food!

411
00:23:43,847 --> 00:23:46,308
H-hey, you guys!

412
00:23:46,391 --> 00:23:48,018
Well then, casually, a sixth one too.

413
00:23:48,101 --> 00:23:50,937
Hey... come on!

414
00:23:51,771 --> 00:23:53,690
Take this. Huh?

415
00:23:54,024 --> 00:23:57,110
Please don't open it until you have all seven.

416
00:23:57,194 --> 00:23:59,279
Huh? Someone died?

417
00:24:01,072 --> 00:24:03,408
This is clearly a suicide.

418
00:24:03,492 --> 00:24:04,868
No. Hmm?

419
00:24:05,285 --> 00:24:07,662
It might be murder. Huh?

420
00:24:08,538 --> 00:24:12,375
So you prepared one outfit... is that what you're saying?

421
00:24:13,335 --> 00:24:15,295
That's... if I remember correctly...

422
00:24:15,821 --> 00:24:17,321
Next Conan,

423
00:24:17,321 --> 00:24:21,221
"The Neighbor at the Site is an Ex-Boyfriend (Part 1)"

424
00:24:37,021 --> 00:24:39,421
Next Conan's Hint:

425
00:24:39,421 --> 00:24:41,221
"Will".

426
00:24:41,258 --> 00:24:42,926
Four suicide notes? Heave-ho.

427
00:24:43,010 --> 00:24:44,803
The Professor's quiz is interesting. Heave-ho...

428
00:24:44,887 --> 00:24:46,221
I slipped...
